## Configuration Options

```toml
[events]
enabled = true
debounce_ms = 500  # Don't fire volume events more than 2x/sec

# Script triggers
[[events.scripts]]
events = ["volume_change"]
script = "~/.config/surface-dial/scripts/volume_light.sh"
timeout_ms = 5000
enabled = true

[[events.scripts]]
events = ["mute_toggle", "mode_change"]
script = "~/.config/surface-dial/scripts/notify.sh"
timeout_ms = 2000
enabled = true

# Webhook triggers
[[events.webhooks]]
events = ["volume_change", "mute_toggle"]
url = "http://homeassistant.local:8123/api/webhook/surface-dial"
method = "POST"
headers = [["Authorization", "Bearer TOKEN"]]
timeout_ms = 3000
enabled = true

[[events.webhooks]]
events = ["battery_change"]
url = "https://api.example.com/dial/battery"
method = "POST"
timeout_ms = 5000
enabled = true
```

## Security Considerations

1. **Script execution** — Only run scripts from config, never arbitrary paths
2. **Webhook URLs** — Warn if using HTTP (not HTTPS) for remote URLs
3. **Timeouts** — Enforce max timeout to prevent hanging
4. **Debouncing** — Prevent spam that could overload external services
5. **Credential handling** — Webhook headers may contain tokens; don't log them

## Dependencies

- Config storage (DIAL-mms) - for event handler settings
- Daemon refactor (DIAL-l6g) - integration point
- `reqwest` crate for HTTP webhooks
- `tokio` for async execution

